A TreeSet is a collection class that stores unique elements in a sorted order. It is part of java.util package that implements the SortedSet interface, and internally uses a Red-Black tree to maintain sorting.

a. Does not allow duplicates and null values. From JDK 7 onward, inserting null throws NullPointerException.
b. Implements the NavigableSet interface and provides navigation methods like higher(), lower(), ceiling() and floor().
c. TreeSet is not synchronized. it must be synchronized using Collections.synchronizedSet().

